# Neumorphism Design System

QuickCalci Formulas uses a neumorphic (soft UI) design system. All new and modified components must follow these rules.

## Required tokens

| Token | Light | Dark |
|-------|-------|------|
| Surface / background | `#E7E5E4` | `#2b2f36` |
| Brand / primary | `#006666` | `#00a3a3` |
| Text | `#1E2938` | `#e8eaed` |
| Secondary | `#F1F2F5` | `#353a42` |
| Success | `#00A63D` | `#00A63D` |
| Warning | `#FE9900` | `#FE9900` |
| Danger | `#FF2157` | `#FF2157` |

Fonts: **Space Mono** (sans + display), **JetBrains Mono** (mono).

## Abstraction layer

1. **CSS utilities** in `src/styles/globals.css`: `.neu-raised`, `.neu-flat`, `.neu-inset`, `.neu-pressed`, `.neu-interactive`, `.neu-divider`
2. **CVA helper** in `src/lib/neu.ts`: `neuVariants({ elevation, shape, interactive })`

## Rules (must)

- Use `neuVariants()` or `.neu-*` classes for all elevation and surface styling
- Keep `background` and `card` the same surface color as the page
- Use semantic CSS variables (`var(--brand)`, `var(--foreground)`, etc.) — never hardcode hex in components
- Provide `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring` on interactive elements
- Use `neu-inset` for inputs, search fields, slider tracks, and pressed states
- Use `neu-raised` for cards, buttons, modals, and elevated panels
- Use `neu-divider` instead of `border-t` / `border-b` for section separators

## Rules (must not)

- Do not use raw `border`, `border-border`, `shadow`, `shadow-lg`, or `box-shadow` in component classNames
- Do not use pure white (`#fff`) or pure black (`#000`) as surface backgrounds
- Do not hardcode shadow values in inline styles
- Do not mix flat/material borders with neumorphic surfaces in the same component

## Component states

Interactive components must handle: default, hover (`neu-interactive` lift), active/pressed (`neu-pressed` or `:active`), focus-visible, disabled, loading, error (as relevant).

## QA checklist (code review)

- [ ] No raw `border` or `box-shadow` in changed files
- [ ] Surfaces use `var(--background)` / `var(--card)` tokens
- [ ] Elevation comes from `neuVariants` or `.neu-*` only
- [ ] Focus rings visible on keyboard navigation
- [ ] Works in both `.light` and `.dark` themes
- [ ] Text contrast meets WCAG AA on surface `#E7E5E4`
- [ ] New React primitives import from `@/lib/neu`
